> Hi, ahmetgunduz:
> I tested the model in online mode with my own video. And all looks fine except if I show the same gesture twice. The model failed to predict the second gesture(no gesture is detected). And I doubt the reason maybe the rule based filter, but I'm not sure. Could you please give me some advice?

@asdfqwer2015 Can you explain how you tested your video on the pretrained model?

@manish2295
  I've only tested my video with my trained model with jester 27 classes with acc > 92%, I've not tested pretrained model from ahmetgunduz. 
  I borrowed rules from https://github.com/ahmetgunduz/Real-time-GesRec/blob/225ec81e97ba09849b5457a98d4ddad00176a50c/online_test.py and I tested 2 different gestures, each gesture 2 times. But the result is that the second time for each gesture has not been detected. While debugging, it seems like all actions have been detected as early detection, but ignored by https://github.com/ahmetgunduz/Real-time-GesRec/blob/225ec81e97ba09849b5457a98d4ddad00176a50c/online_test.py#L316
